Renamed 14.7.1998 to become the parish of Aintree Village. 
    See also Table 2, notes (a), (e) and (f).

Created 14.7.1998 by renaming the parish of Aintree. 
    See also Table 2, note (h).
Renamed 19.11.1987 to become the parish of Little Altcar.

Created 1.4.2004 out of the Sefton unparished area 
    and the parish of Little Altcar. See also Table 2, note (h).

Created 1.4.2000 out of the Sefton unparished area. 
    See also Table 2, note (h).

Created 19.11.1987 by renaming the parish of Altcar in Merseyside. 
    See also Table 2, note (h).

Abolished 1.4.1982 and divided between the parishes of 
    Aintree and Sefton. See also Table 2, note (b).

Unparished areas of the towns of Bootle, Crosby, Formby, 
    Litherland, Seaforth and Waterloo. See also Table 2, notes (a), (b), (e), (f), (g) and (h).
